male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2-5</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Head and thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2-5</figureCitation>
) longer than pronotum and mesonotum combined (1.45:1). Vertex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3</figureCitation>
) with median carina very faint, only conspicuous at apex and base; lateral carinate margins sinuate. Frons (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3</figureCitation>
) with lateral carinae reaching to front of eyes. Pronotum (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">5</figureCitation>
) with median carina distinct, lateral carinae very faint. Mesonotum (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Taxonomic history of the genus Saigona Matsumura, 1010 (uploaded from Bourgoin 2021). For each synonymized genus, their protonyms are in blue boxes, and the current valid name of the genus is in green. Red vertical arrows illustrate synonymy and the red cross the status revivisco of the genus Leprota Melichar, 1912." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574422" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2</figureCitation>
) tricarinate on disc, lateral carinae curved towards median carinate at the front. Fore wings (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–5" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 5. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen sp. nov. 2 male, holotype, dorsal view 3 male, head and thorax, dorsal view 4 male, head, frons and clypeus, lateral view 5 male, head and pronotum, lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (2 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures2-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574423" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 6 forewing 7 hindwing 8 genitalia, lateral view 9 pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view 10 pygofer and anal tube, dorsal view 11 aedeagus, lateral view 12 aedeagus, ventral view 13 aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (6 - 10), 0.5 mm (11 - 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574424" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">6</figureCitation>
) hyaline with ScP+R, MP and Cu branched apically, longer than widest part, with length to maximum width ratio of 3.0; stigma distinct, with 3 or 4 cells, veins with numerous fuscous setae. costal margin distinctly expanded into a narrow, sclerotized costal area, without transverse veins; ScP+R branched apically; MP bifurcating into MP1+2 and MP3+4 at basal 3/5 and beyond CuA; CuA forked near middle of forewing; 13 apical marginal cells between RP and CuA; Pcu and A1 fusing at apical 2/5 of clavus. Hindwings (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 6 forewing 7 hindwing 8 genitalia, lateral view 9 pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view 10 pygofer and anal tube, dorsal view 11 aedeagus, lateral view 12 aedeagus, ventral view 13 aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (6 - 10), 0.5 mm (11 - 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574424" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">7</figureCitation>
) well developed, legs moderately elongate, fore femora flattened and dilated; hind tibiae with 5 or 6 lateral black-tipped spines and 8 apical black-tipped teeth, spinal formula 8/(10-12)/(10-12).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
Male 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pygofer (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 6 forewing 7 hindwing 8 genitalia, lateral view 9 pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view 10 pygofer and anal tube, dorsal view 11 aedeagus, lateral view 12 aedeagus, ventral view 13 aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (6 - 10), 0.5 mm (11 - 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574424" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">8-10</figureCitation>
) large and broad in lateral view, posterior margin with a rounded lobe at level of venter of anal tube. Gonostyli (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Saigona baiseensis Zheng &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 6 forewing 7 hindwing 8 genitalia, lateral view 9 pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view 10 pygofer and anal tube, dorsal view 11 aedeagus, lateral view 12 aedeagus, ventral view 13 aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (6 - 10), 0.5 mm (11 - 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.67004.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574424" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">8</figureCitation>
, 
